CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 13, 1957, pg. 1, reads: "'I Asked You Myself...' - Councilman Paul F. Jones, center, reminds Homer Greene, director of the Department of Lands and Buildings, left, and J. Clyde Taylor, superintendent of the Bureau of Building Inspection, right, that he made a personal request that action can be taken to clean up the lot opposite Miller St. School which Mr. Jones called 'an attractive nuisance.' - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Homer Greene, Paul F. Jones, and J. Clyde Taylor seated around table in Pittsburgh City Council Chambers, City County Building
